{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require full public consultation on proposed PIP reforms in the Green Paper",
        "additional_details": "Excluding any of the changes denies affected individuals and organisations the chance to provide feedback.\r\n\r\nThe Green Paper proposes changes to the daily living component eligibility of PIP without public consultation. We believe that the proposed changes will make it harder for those with significant difficulties across multiple activities to qualify for support.\r\n\r\nWe believe these reforms risk removing vital support without scrutiny and call on the Government to urgently commit to a full, transparent consultation before the Green Paper closes on 30 June 2025, ensuring disabled people's views are heard.",
        "background": "The Government must include all proposed changes to PIP in the Pathways to Work Green Paper in the consultation, including the four-point threshold rule for PIP. The significant reforms will directly impact disabled people.",
